sequenceDiagram
    participant Konflux as Konflux CI/CD
    participant Cachi2 as cachi2/Hermeto<br/>Prefetch
    participant Registry as registry.redhat.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as rhods-operator
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Controller as odh-notebook-controller
    participant Gateway as Gateway/Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as JupyterLab<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Culler as Notebook Culler

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Konflux,Registry: Flow 1: Hermetic Image Build
        Konflux->>Cachi2: Prefetch RPMs, pip wheels, npm packages<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        Cachi2-->>Konflux: /cachi2/output/deps/ (local mount)
        Konflux->>Konflux: Build image (air-gapped, no network)
        Konflux->>Registry: Push built image<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    end

    rect rgb(245, 255, 245)
        Note over Operator,Dashboard: Flow 2: Workbench Deployment
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ImageStream from manifests/rhoai/<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
        Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Read ImageStream annotations<br/>opendatahub.io/notebook-image-*
        User->>Dashboard: Select workbench image
        Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS mTLS (User OIDC token)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Mutating webhook fires<br/>Inject kube-rbac-proxy sidecar
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Mount CA bundle + DSPA secret
        K8sAPI->>Registry: Pull workbench image<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+ (pull secret)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 250, 240)
        Note over User,S3: Flow 3: User Workbench Access
        User->>Gateway: Access /notebook/{ns}/{user}/<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        Gateway->>RBAC: Forward request
        RBAC->>RBAC: Validate OAuth/OIDC token
        RBAC->>Jupyter: Proxy to JupyterLab<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
        Jupyter-->>User: JupyterLab UI (WebSocket)
        Jupyter->>S3: Access data<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+ (AWS creds)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 245)
        Note over Culler,Jupyter: Flow 4: Idle Culling
        Culler->>Jupyter: GET /api/kernels/<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
        Jupyter-->>Culler: Kernel status JSON
        Note over Culler: If idle > threshold → scale to 0
    end
